            <div class="zcenter">
                <h1>Recommended for caretakers</h1>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="center">
            <p style="width: 75%; font-size: 20px;">Articles addressing cyber safety and security aimed at caretakers to aid them in helping children navigate the digital world.</p>
        <div class="card-container">
            <ul class="card-wrapper">
                <li class="card reveal fade-bottom">
                    <img class="card-img" src='/img/adult-child-talking.jpeg'>
                    <h3><a href="/caretakers-articles/cyber-education-cyberbullying">Cyber Education & Cyberbullying</a></h3>
                    <p>It's important to educate children about cyber safety to mitigate and prevent cyberbullying. Teach them to be kind and report any bullying.</p>
                </li>
                <li class="card reveal fade-bottom">
                    <img class="card-img" src='/img/adult-on-phone.jpeg'>
                    <h3><a href="/caretakers-articles/monitoring-children">Monitoring Children</a></h3>
                    <p>Monitor children means to watch and check what they do online and offline. It helps to keep them safe.</p>
                </li>
                <li class="card reveal fade-bottom">
                    <img class="card-img" src='/img/adult-children-tablet.jpeg'>
                    <h3><a href="/caretakers-articles/parental-control-guidance">Parental Control & Guidance</a></h3>
                    <p>Parental control and guidance are useful to help minimise the risks your child may face. It’s important to teach your child skills like critical thinking and resilience, and encourage them to talk to you about anything they find upsetting online.</p>
                </li>
            </ul>
